      <div class="subtext">
          <h1>Catch that Raccoon!!</h1>
          <h3>December 2020</h3><br>
          <p class="top">I have some experience with web design and development. This is thanks to some of the courses I have taken at RIT. In case I need to sell you on the premise for, "Catch that Raccoon," the game is like Pacman and Snake where you get to play as a Raccoon stealing trash bags. You have to narrowly avoid a crew of police officers. The game was built utilizing a prexisting template called DOM! Adventure. However, I will clarify that the AI movement, random world generation, gameplay elements, and asset work was devloped by myself using javascript.</p>
          <p><a href="https://people.rit.edu/tml1957/235/project3/"class="viewLink">Click Here to Play Catch That Raccoon!!</a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="subimg">
          <img src="/assets/img/ct.png" alt="Screenshot from Crunch Time">
