      <div class="subtext">
          <h1>Mathematical Jousting</h1>
          <h3>March 2021 - May 2021</h3><br>
          <p class="top">Mathematical Jousting is an educational board game I developed with three friends for my Game Design and Development class at RIT. Our primary objective was to create a simple game that you can play anywhere so long as you have a couple dice lying around. The game involves a lot of dice rolling and quick mental math. Despite its simplicity, it is probably one of the most intense games I've helped make as dice get to be thrown around the room and arguments will break out. My main goal with this project was to test and refine the experience to make sure it was as simple and fun as possible.</p>
